# CvilleEats App

CvilleEats is a web-based restaurant finder and review application for Charlottesville, VA. Users can browse restaurants, view details, leave reviews, save favorites, and filter by dietary preferences and open hours. Admins can approve submitted restaurants and edit restaurant details.

## Team Members
- Krishna Mishra (ysv7yj)
- Anvitha Bandam (hnr6zp)
- Aleesha Khurram (wma9tt)

## Tech Stack
- PHP (session auth, PDO prepared statements)
- MySQL 
- Apache (XAMPP locally, GCP VM for deployment)
- HTML / CSS

## Features
- User registration and login with hashed passwords (bcrypt)
- Restaurant browsing with search, sort, dietary filter, and Open Now filter
- Restaurant detail pages with cuisine tags, opening hours, phone, and dietary info
- Write, edit, and delete reviews with 1–5 star ratings
- Like other users' reviews
- Save/unsave favorite restaurants
- Submit new restaurants for admin approval
- Admin approval workflow for pending restaurants
- Admin restaurant editing (name, address, hours, phone, cuisines, dietary flags)
- Role-based access control (admin vs regular user)
- CSRF protection on all admin actions
- Least-privilege DB users (`cville_app`, `cville_dev_read`, `cville_dev_write`)

## Project Structure
```
auth/               Authentication pages (login, signup, logout)
includes/           Shared includes (connect-db.php, header.php)
assets/css/         Stylesheet (style.css)
add-restaurant.php  Submit a new restaurant for approval
admin-approvals.php Admin: review pending restaurant submissions
approve.php         Admin: process approval of a pending restaurant
edit-restaurant.php Admin: edit an existing restaurant's details
explore.php         Browse and filter all restaurants
home.php            Landing/home page
profile.php         User profile page
restaurant.php      Restaurant detail page (hours, reviews, likes)
review.php          Write or edit a review
saved-restaurants.php  User's saved/favorited restaurants
CvilleEats.sql      Full DB schema, seed data, and security setup
```

## Database Schema

User(<u>User_ID</u>, Username, Email, Password_Hash, Is_Admin, Date_Created)  
Restaurant(<u>Restaurant_ID</u>, Restaurant_Name, Price_Level, Street, <u>Zip_Code</u>, Vegetarian_Options, Vegan_Options, GlutenFree_Options)  
Location(<u>Zip_Code</u>, City, State)  
Cuisine(<u>Cuisine_ID</u>, Cuisine_Name)  
Review(<u>Review_ID</u>, Review_Date, Comment, Rating, <u>User_ID</u>, <u>Restaurant_ID</u>)  
Opening_Hours({<u>Restaurant_ID</u>, <u>Day_Of_Week</u>}, Open_Time, Close_Time)  
Restaurant_Phone(<u>Restaurant_ID</u>, <u>Phone_Number</u>)  
Has_Cuisine(<u>Restaurant_ID</u>, <u>Cuisine_ID</u>)  
Favorite(<u>User_ID</u>, <u>Restaurant_ID</u>, Date_Saved)  
Review_Like(<u>User_ID</u>, <u>Review_ID</u>, Liked_At)

## How to Run Locally
1. Start Apache and MySQL in XAMPP.
2. Place the project folder inside `htdocs/`.
3. Import `CvilleEats.sql` into phpMyAdmin (it drops/recreates the DB).
4. Visit: `http://localhost/cville-eats/auth/login.php`

## Live Deployment
`http://34.26.135.79/cville-eats/auth/login.php`

To promote a user to admin, run in MySQL:
```sql
UPDATE User SET Is_Admin = 1 WHERE Username = 'your_username';
```

## Security
- Passwords hashed with `password_hash` (bcrypt) at signup; verified with `password_verify` at login
- All DB queries use PDO prepared statements (no raw user input in SQL)
- Session regenerated on login and logout
- CSRF tokens on all admin POST actions
- Least-privilege DB users configured in `CvilleEats.sql` 

## Deployment
Deployed on GCP (Ubuntu VM) with Apache and PHP.
Database name: `CvilleEats`
